comments: Jackson (LAC) establishes himself in Caruso's (CHI) path and slightly extends his arm to his Caruso's side as they disengage.
Batum (LAC) establishes himself in Caruso's (CHI) path as he hands off the ball and is firming up when contact occurs.
Leonard (LAC) briefly places his arm against Vucevic (CHI) and immediately slides his arm off as they  engage and disengage with one another.
Batum (LAC) legally contests DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Vucevic (CHI) briefly places his hand to Leonard's (LAC) shoulder underneath the rim and disengages sliding his hand off.
Williams (CHI) is moving alongside George's (LAC) path and marginal body contact occurs during George's (LAC) drive.
Williams (CHI) brings his arm toward George's (LAC) side and marginal contact occurs during George's drive.
Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in Jackson's (LAC) path and marginal contact occurs as they disengage.
Powell (LAC) defends Caruso (CHI) off-ball and briefly places his hands against Caruso before correcting.
Caruso (CHI) establishes himself in Leonard's (LAC) path and absorbs the contact.
Powell (LAC) makes contact with LaVine's (CHI) elbow during his upward shooting motion, and the contact affects his jump shot attempt.
Powell (LAC) establishes himself in Williams's (CHI) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Vucevic (CHI) already in Leonard's (LAC) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together and Leonard releases his pass attempt.
Powell (LAC) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Jackson (LAC) reaches in and makes contact to DeRozan's (CHI) left arm and affects his driving shot attempt.
Williams (CHI) extends his arm and lightly brushes Jackson's (LAC) arm during his drive in transition.
Jackson (LAC) establishes himself in Williams' (CHI) path and they both engage and disengage with one another as the pick is set.
null
DeRozan (CHI) moves laterally into George's (LAC) path and initiates body contact that affects George's SQBR during the drive and prior to his gather.
Caruso (CHI) takes longer than 5 seconds to release the inbounds pass.
Vucevic (CHI) has his arms slightly extended as he sets the screen and marginal contact occurs with George (LAC) as they disengage.

Replay review of the foul called on DeRozan (CHI) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Caruso (CHI) initiates contact with Powell's (LAC) wrist, and the contact affects his driving shot attempt.
Leonard (LAC) makes contact with the ball and dislodges it away from LaVine (CHI) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Vucevic (CHI) commits a take foul on Leonard (LAC). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime
Batum (LAC) grasps and then releases Vucevic's (CHI) jersey off-ball.
George (LAC) legally contests DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot attempt.
